BBC.Later.Live.with.Jools.Holland.S44E02.1080i.h264-NX

BBC 2 HD Tuesday 22nd April 2014

Jools Holland is joined in the studio by Glasgow's Paolo Nutini, who returns after a five year break to perform tracks from his new long player, Caustic Love. Royal Blood make their Later debut with their formula of heavy blues riffs and rock choruses. Neil Finn pops in to play selections from his new Dizzy Heights album. Plus, New York-based singer songwriter Joan Wasser, better known as Joan as Police Woman, Brooklyn five-piece Lucius, with songs from their Wildewoman album, and Zara McFarlane with her take on Police and Thieves.
